description: For sale: $369,900. Enjoy ultimate privacy with Girard Lake Park in your backyard! Renovated top to bottom with quality materials and finishes. description: Recently sold: $369,900.

Recently sold: $380,000. 3008 W 100th St, Bloomington, MN is a single family home that contains 1,374 sq ft and was built in 1969. It contains 4 bedrooms and 1 bathroom. This home last sold for $380,000 in March 2020. 
 
The Zestimate for this house is $374,064, which has increased by $19,582 in the last 30 days. The Rent Zestimate for this home is $2,195/mo, which has increased by $73/mo in the last 30 days.

Recently sold: $400,000. CASUAL ELEGANCE AT ITS FINEST!  
IN BRIEF - Fabulous 'better than new' fully renovated townhome features high-end updates, neutral finishes, spacious living areas with built-ins and high ceilings, and 3 large bedrooms (each with private bath and custom closet)!  Enjoy the luxury of a worry-free lifestyle at an affordable price.  Homeowner association dues ($305.55 per month) cover Comcast cable TV; garbage and recycling; lawn care and snow removal; exterior maintenance; insurance and professional management.
 
ACCESS - Easy access to the front porch and entrance, with sidewalk and guest parking right outside the front door and NO steps to navigate.

FINE FINISHES - New Bambu porcelain tile in the spacious foyer leads to new Brazilian walnut floors throughout the main floor and luxurious Masland carpeting leading to bedrooms.  The great room features bright windows and slider to the deck plus a full wall of built-in cabinets with a gas fireplace.  The walk-through kitchen has granite counters, natural stone tile backsplash, pull-out cabinet accessories, pantry closet, counter-height breakfast bar, and new stainless steel sink and appliances.  Maple cabinets, doors, trim and matching wood blinds throughout the house are accented by beautiful new light fixtures, chandeliers and combination ceiling fans/lights.  All bathrooms have porcelain tile, and the main floor powder room has a sleek pedestal sink.

CONVENIENCE - The layout offers maximum flexibility with a huge (13?x23?) great room and a spacious front room ideal for formal dining, den, office, or playroom.  A sliding patio door leads to a covered balcony or deck with convenient natural gas connection for barbecue grill and lots of seating space.  

UPSTAIRS - The master suite includes a 13? x 23? bedroom with plenty of room for a sitting area, a spacious bathroom with granite-top double-sink vanity and new tiled shower with frameless glass door.  The oversized walk-in closet is outfitted with custom racks, shelves and drawers for maximum storage.  The second bedroom has ensuite bath with granite-topped vanity, a window, and combination tub/shower. It has its own walk-in closet with custom closet system.  A laundry room equipped with laundry tub, cabinets, washer and dryer completes the upper floor.

DOWNSTAIRS - Enter the lower level through the private tuck-under 2-car finished garage with epoxied floor into the tiled mudroom with closet.  The lower level offers the third bedroom with closet, daylight windows, and its own en-suite 3/4 bath with granite-topped vanity and linen closet. A utility room with new water heater, furnace/air conditioner and humidifier completes the lower level.
  
OTHER FEATURES - State-of-the-art security system.  The home was meticulously maintained, with no smoking, children or pets.  Furnishings for sale separately include king bedroom set from Boston Interiors, four counter-height bar stools from Italy, Weber gas grill, and wall-mounted televisions.

LOCATION - The Village on Nine Mile Creek townhome and condominium community is conveniently located along Old Shakopee Road with easy access to local shopping, entertainment, churches, and medical as well as the rest of the Twin Cities.  The Bloomington Civic Center, Creekside Community Center and community gardens are all within walking distance.   Enjoy the Saturday Farmers Market and Artistry exhibits and performances.  Seniors can enjoy meals and activities at the community center.  In addition, the adjacent Nine Mile Creek Senior Living facility makes many of its facilities available to Village on Nine Mile Creek residents - from the fitness center to meals and movies to extra parking garage space.
The bus stops less than a block away, and interstate highway 35W access is within one mile.  
The community has direct access into Moir Park with many miles of walking trails for people and pets along lovely Nine Mile Creek.
MLS #5332271

description:
Recently sold: $380,000. OPEN HOUSE: SAT, JAN 4th 12:30 - 2:30 PM.

Welcome home!

Home meets the perfect checklist:

1. Location ? - Desirable Tretbaugh Heights neighborhood in West Bloomington
2. Lot ? - Spacious .61 acre lot surrounded by mature trees, flat backyard, bonfire pit and resurfaced tennis / basketball court
3. School ? - 271 Bloomington schools
4. Home ? - High quality, completely remodeled and well maintained one story home
5. Lifestyle ? - Steps to Girard Park, seconds from shopping and dining at France & 90th, minutes to the airport, vibrant Downtown Minneapolis or charming St. Paul

This stunning one story home is completely remodeled with an open floor plan.  Entertainers dream kitchen with tons of natural light, grand island space, and stone Quartz counter-tops.

Nearly new head-to-toe with a newer roof and siding, stainless steel appliances, gleaming hardwood floors, alluring light fixtures, radon removal system, new front windows, walk-out sliding doors to oversized backyard.  Freshly painted interior, white trim throughout home and warm wainscoting on stairs and custom built-in mudroom area.  

Relax in the recently updated and cozy basement with light dimmers, extra fluffy carpet and electric fireplace.  Or work away in private lower level office with door closed.

Home features outside deck perfect for your evening BBQ's, extra storage with shed.  There are 3 bedrooms all on one level, master 1/2 bathroom, and updated basement bedroom ideal for a guest get-a-way or teenager retreat with full updated bath.  

Don't miss this gem . . .

description:
Recently sold: $464,000. Enjoy watching amazing sunsets and soaring eagles with westerly views across the lake! Updated 4 bed, 3 bath 2 story with over 100 feet of shoreline on
Lower Penn Lake in Bloomington. Lot is over 1/2 acre. Brand new carpet
upstairs and down, fresh paint, beautiful hardwood on main level. Many newer Andersen windows and patio doors. Wood burning fireplace that has been inspected and certified. Large deck off main floor plus sitting balcony off the large master bedroom. Walkout lower level family room for easy access to the on ground pool surrounded by deck. Newer white eat in kitchen with huge pantry closet and center island. Lower level also includes a sound proof music room that could be a 5th bedroom, movie room, game room for loud teenagers, etc. Large yard with shade trees, private shoreline and the perfect sledding hill. Huge storage space for mowers, pool toys, etc. accessible from the back patio. Paddle boat and marshmallows to roast over the bonfire included.

description:
Recently sold: $245,000. Contact the listing agents, Welu Home Team, for the most accurate and up-to-date information. 612-207-1815 or marina@weluhometeam.com

Welcome home! Rambler in West Bloomington with tons of original charm and large, flat, very shaded lot! Only a few blocks from Valley West Shopping Center - feat Cub Foods, Caribou, Willy McCoys, Chipotle and more! Three bedrooms conveniently located on main level - the living is easy! Original hardwood floors run thoughout the main level and are under the carpet in the living room. Dedicated dining room with bay window and open to the kitchen for excellent flow in daily living. Enjoy the large, open Family Room in the basement, complete with 3/4 bath. Could add an additional bedroom if desired by adding egress window, etc. Cedar clad sauna is added bonus in basement - combat the winter chill with your own personal spa! Mid century charm throughout with updates in all the right places.

description: Recently sold: $284,500.

Recently sold: $262,500. Perfect home for families or empty-nesters located in desirable west Bloomington. 

Four bedrooms, two bathrooms with updated kitchen, great room and dining area. Kitchen includes dining nook, mom's desk and large walk-in pantry. Finished basement with laundry room/tubs, family room, storage room, bathroom and optional fourth bedroom or exercise room.




Neighborhood Description



Desirable west Bloomington location between Dwan Golf Course and Westwood Elementary School. Perfect home for young families or empty-nesters. Award winning school district - Westwood Elementary, Olson Middle School and Jefferson High School. Immaculately cared for inside and out. Ten minutes to Southdale Mall, 20 minutes to downtown Minneapolis and the University of Minnesota and 15 minutes to Mall of America. Local shopping within 5-minute walk includes Cub Foods, Walgreens, Caribou Coffee, MGM Liquor, Chipotle and many other popular retail stores shops and restaurants.

Recently sold: $371,000. Fabulous one-level living in the tree-lined Penn Glen neighborhood of Bloomington.  Architect remodel and addition created a light-filled main-level master suite and spacious lower level family room.  Expanded performance kitchen sports granite countertops and stainless Meile, Bosch and KitchenAid appliances. Main floor complete with hardwood floors, two additional bedrooms, laundry, linen closet and pantry. Completely updated sky-lit guest bathroom. Additional lower level bedroom and 3/4 bath, plus office/hobby/rec/storage spaces and workshop. Updated mechanicals, windows, Hardie plank siding and roof make this ready to live in immediately! Two-car garage, ample front and back yards and secluded deck.  Easy access to freeway and all types of shopping.  Just five minutes to the Mall of America and the airport.

Recently sold: $298,900. Fantastic 4 BR/3 BA home on large lot in prime location. Clean Bloomington time of sale report. Roof - 2014. Great space, 3 BR's on 1 level, LL family room with fireplace and bedroom. Clean oversized 2 car garage. Huge deck.

description:
Recently sold: $309,152. Will be posted in the near future; updating with fresh paint in many of the rooms, and new flooring in the 3 season porch.

This move in ready, 3 bedroom, 1.5 bath home boasts a as a large, vaulted ceiling living room with tall full length windows, an updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances, and a full sized formal dining room with a west facing bay window for spectacular sunset. There is hardwood floor in the living room, dining room and beneath the freshly carpeted bedrooms on the main floor

The electric panel was updated with new breakers in 2015, along with a high efficiency furnace and water heater.  The bathroom on the main level had a brand new tub/shower installed in 2017.


The attached, oversized 2 car garage has plenty of loft storage and is connected to the home via an oversized 3 season porch that can easily be used as a mud room.  The fully enclosed porch leads out into a 16'x32' ground level deck that overlooks the spacious, secluded back yard with a gorgeous treeline, ground bushes, a fire pit and city legal 8x8 wooden storage shed.

The fully finished basement has a workshop, floor drain tile with sump pump, 1/2 bath, laundry room, oversized bedroom, office with plenty of closet space and an entertainment room.

description: Recently sold: $400,000. An opportunity to own a truly unique home. Built in 1950 as a state of the art custom home. It was purchased by a Master woodworker in 1995. Renovations are about 85% complete and include: custom kitchen in art deco style, asian inspired master suite addition, with 17x17 bedroom and upscale amenities such as tray ceiling in bedroom, mitered barrel ceiling in hallway, gas fireplace in bath and bedroom, spa tub and huge walk-in closet/dressing room. Cabinetry and trim are of fine and exotic woods such as African wenge, Bolivian rosewood, English sycamore and walnut. Living  room is large enough to accommodate a 5'9" baby grand (for sale). The lot is partially wooded and private. Feels like up north when sitting around the fire pit. This is very comfortable living all on one level, however, should you need more space the 2000 sq ft unfinished basement with wood fireplace and egress window should be of interest. Easy walk to elem. school, library and shops. 10-12 min. to downtown.

description:
Recently sold: $285,000. **OPEN HOUSE, SATURDAY, JUNE 16, NOON-2PM**

Don't miss out on this beautifully updated 4 bedroom home with 3 BEDROOMS ON ONE LEVEL.  Come enjoy the beautiful hardwood floors with that will lead you into a freshly painted kitchen and take a moment to notice the newer appliances.  As you walk to the THREE bedrooms on one level notice the huge picture window bringing in tons of natural light!  Take time to stop in the completely remodeled bathroom and pay attention to the tile work!  As you imaging your family in these bedrooms and observe the newer windows!!  Now that you have explored the main level its time to explore the downstairs.  As you walk down the stairs pay attention to the care that the owners took with the ceilings!  As you walk into the family room observe the fireplace with near by egress window letting in ample nature light.  Imagine your family having family movie night down here!  As you look over your shoulder to the back side of the room you will notice the workout area! Finally, not to be out done there is a master/guest suite; this large bedroom with attached bathroom would make for a wonderful master bedroom or a great place for the out of town family!  The downstairs bathroom has been completely remodeled and even has a Bluetooth Speaker/FAN!  Come enjoy a BBQ on the paver patio backyard.  

Owners have updated Furnace, AC and Roof come and take a visit and see all the things that we were unable to list!!

description: Recently sold: $376,500.

Newer high efficiency furnace and air conditioner with programmable thermostat and recently added attic insulation.
